1 (i) a mental health facility as provided in 53-21-102;
2 (ii) an assisted living facility licensed under 50-5-227;
3 (iii) a long-term care facility, an adult day-care center, a mental health center, a medical assistance
4 facility, or a nonprofit health care facility as provided in 50-5-101;
5 (iv) a community group home for developmentally disabled, mentally disabled, or severely disabled
6 persons that does not provide skilled or intermediate nursing care;
7 (v) a licensed adult foster family care home;
8 (vi) a halfway house operated in accordance with regulations of the department of public health
9 and human services for the rehabilitation of alcoholics or drug-dependent persons;
10 (vii) a youth foster home, a kinship foster home, a youth shelter care facility, a transitional living
11 program, or a youth group home as provided in 52-2-602;
12 (viii) a day-care center, a day-care facility, a family day-care home, or a group day-care home as
13 provided in 52-2-703; or
14 (ix) a public or nonpublic school.
15 (b) "Vulnerable person" means:
16 (i) a child;
17 (ii) a vulnerable adult as provided in 52-3-803; or
18 (iii) an incapacitated person as provided in 72-5-101.
19
20 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Codification instruction. [Sections 1 and 2] are intended to be codified
21 as an integral part of Title 46, chapter 18, part 2, and the provisions of Title 46, chapter 18, part 2, apply to
22 [sections 1 and 2].
